value.0: Heh. Not me, but maybe a friend. You see, a good buddy of mine, Terari went on an expedition with the other druids to try to save the Spirit of the Wood.
None of them has returned, ya see. I'd venture out and save his sorry hide but I ain't allowed to leave the camp. I owe him, and if you help us out, then I'll owe ya.
Fine. Just keep your eyes open for a skinny elf man then, would ya?
Alright, best of luck to you. Let me know if you find anything.
Ha! Always like him to get tangled up with something like the sirines. Poor bastard's told me all about it. Anyways, here's some coin for ya, as promised. Ya did get him out in one piece.
Har har! Tis always like you to get into trouble with the ladies, eh Terari?
<StartAction>[Sigh.]</Start> You'll never let me hear the end of it, will you?
What do you mean by protecting nature?
I can look for your friend.
